HEADWORD: Incomer
<hw>In"com`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
comes in.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Outgoers and <qex>incomers</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Lew
Wallace.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who succeeds another, as a tenant of land,
houses, etc.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incoming</ent>⟦br⟧
